## The loop (from harness-orchestrator)

```
Decompose the requirement into ordered, independently-verifiable tasks
For each task:
  ground  → harness-context-loader builds the brief + acceptance criteria
  plan    → state the approach and files to touch
  build   → implement, following project patterns
  verify  → harness-verifier runs this project's real gates; fix on red
  test    → add + run tests until green
```

## Project-specific choices

- **Parallelism:** {e.g. "build independent tasks in parallel via subagents; keep DB-migration tasks serial".}
- **Definition of done:** {e.g. "verifier green + tests passing + changelog updated".}
- **Out of scope for auto-build:** {e.g. "never touch infra/ or secrets without asking".}

## Quality gates

Defer to the project's own commands (see CLAUDE.md). The verifier marks any gate the
project doesn't define as "not configured" rather than inventing one.

## Run log

The orchestrator may append a short summary of each run to `.claude/harness-journal.md`
(requirement, tasks completed, what was generated, what's still open) so work can resume later.
